summary: SummaryCharlotte Tilbury's award-winning Hollywood Contour Wand is an easy-to-use, super-flattering cream contour wand that creates sculpted cheekbones in seconds. Charlotte has studied the undertones of different skin tones to create balanced shades so everyone can find their match!
details: DetailsBenefitsHollywood Contour Wands makes contouring easySuper-flattering soft-sculpt effectLayers & blends flawlessly over liquid and powder makeup for long-lasting wear that doesn't crease or set into fine linesFeaturesFool-proof, precision-tip cream contour wandPro-grip technology for a long-lasting, natural finishKey IngredientsLindera Root Essence for smoother & revitalized skinItem 2619436How To UseTo use, start by sucking in your cheekbones, sweeping the magic cushion applicator on the hollows in a horizontal line towards your hairline.Apply in vertical stripes on the sides of your nose and loop underneath, then apply on the sides of your forehead, temples and jawline.Finish by applying on the eye crease to fake a deeper socket, then use the Hollywood Complexion Brush (sold separately) to buff and blend it all in for a seamless finish.IngredientsMedium-Tan: Water, Cyclopentasiloxane, Isododecane, Mica, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Polyglyceryl-4 Diisostearate/Polyhydroxystearate/Sebacate, Triethylhexanoin, Phenylisopropyl Dimethicone, Glycerin, Silica, Hydrogenated Starch Hydrolysate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Hydroxyacetophenone, Sodium Chloride, Alcohol, 1,2-Hexanediol, Caprylyl Glycol, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Lindera Strychnifolia Root Extract, Phenoxyethanol, Ethylhexylglycerin, May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: To use, start by sucking in your cheekbones, sweeping the magic cushion applicator on the hollows in a horizontal line towards your hairline.Apply in vertical stripes on the sides of your nose and loop underneath, then apply on the sides of your forehead, temples and jawline.Finish by applying on the eye crease to fake a deeper socket, then use the Hollywood Complexion Brush (sold separately) to buff and blend it all in for a seamless finish.

reviews.headline: A must-have for effortless sculpting!
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I received this product from @influenster in exchange for an honest review!

I finally got my hands on the Charlotte Tilbury Hollywood Contour Wand in Medium, and now I understand the hype. The formula is incredibly creamy and blends like a dream. Whether I use a brush, sponge, or even my fingers, it melts into the skin so naturally and gives me the perfect contoured look‚Äîdefined but never harsh.

The Medium shade works beautifully on my skin tone‚Äîit's neutral, not too warm or muddy, and gives that soft shadow effect without looking fake. I love the built-in cushion applicator too; it makes applying the product super easy and precise, especially when I'm in a rush.

A little goes a long way, so even though the tube isn't huge, it lasts me a while. The only small downside is the price‚Äîit's definitely a splurge‚Äîbut for the quality, I think it's 100% worth it.

If you're looking for a contour product that's beginner-friendly but gives professional results, this is it. I'll definitely be repurchasing!

reviews.headline: I use daily!
reviews.comments: I love this contour stick. It's more of a bronzer and it looks heavenly! It blends in like butter and adds the perfect touch of warmth. The packaging is super convenient and it doesn't have a harsh annoying scent so I know it won't break me out. Over all I love it

reviews.headline: Contour of the summer
reviews.comments: A great contour wand! I have dry skin and this formula works really well for me. It's pretty easy to blend and melts into the skin. I love the applicator! It makes it easy to build up for a more or less dramatic look. This will be my contour of the summer!

reviews.headline: Great color

reviews.headline: Easily create definition

The packaging is not ideal because it has a foam tip that loads with product.  I find that to be he central and dislike using these products after a couple uses for this reason.

reviews.headline: Beautiful Contour
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This contour has an easy to use applicator and blends like a dream! It has buildable color so you can tailor it to whatever look you are going for! Would definitely recommend for every day and glam!

reviews.headline: Helped me learn contour
reviews.comments: This product is so easy to use! I was scared of contour but after seeing this at a CT event at our local store I fell in love. It is easy to apply, blend, and build up. I also find it hard to find contour for my skin tone and am happy that this is in a shade range for me.

reviews.headline: Effortless contouring and so easy to use
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I'm a big fan of Charlotte Tilbury wands, and this contour wand made me fall in love with the brand even more.
The creamy texture and perfect pigmentation make it so easy to use and blend seamlessly with the rest of my makeup.

For someone like me, who has always struggled with contouring, this truly feels like a magic wand. Even if you're not a pro at makeup, you can still achieve a flawless finish with this gem.

reviews.headline: Efficient and effective contouring

I cannot recommend this product enough ‚Äì especially if you were short on time and want a quick contour solution.

reviews.headline: Great!

reviews.headline: Blends like a dream
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I use a ton of Charlotte product but never tried to contour wand. This product blends like a dream and has actual contour colors and that bronzer hue. I can actually carve in cheekbones that'll look like a shadow and it doesn't pick up my foundation when I blend which is hard to find. Deep pigment with little to no scent. You can layer it for a sharper look or buff it out for a natural look. My only gripe is the applicator is messy and hard to keep sanitary. I spray it down with alcohol to clean, but there is a product loss due to that. Overall, great contour.

faceoff_positive.comments:
The Charlotte Tilbury Hollywood Contour Wand has garnered a lot of praise for its ease of use and beautiful results. Here's an overall review based on its features, benefits, and performance:

Pros:
1. Fool-Proof Application: The precision-tip applicator makes it easy to apply contour exactly where you want it, making it ideal for both makeup beginners and pros.
2. Natural Finish: The contour creates a soft-sculpt effect that mimics natural shadows, giving your face a beautifully sculpted look without feeling too harsh or overdone.
3. Blend-ability: It blends flawlessly into both liquid and powder makeup without caking, creasing, or settling into fine lines, ensuring a smooth, even finish throughout the day.
4. Long-Lasting Wear: Thanks to the pro-grip technology, the contour stays in place for hours, even in humid conditions, without requiring touch-ups.
5. Skin Benefits: The addition of Lindera Root Essence helps to smooth and revitalize the skin, adding a bit of skincare goodness to your makeup routine.

Cons:
1. Price: The product is on the pricier side compared to other contour products, making it less accessible for some.
2. Shade Range: While the product works well for many skin tones, some users have noted that the shade range could be more inclusive.

The Hollywood Contour Wand is a standout product, especially for those who want an effortless, natural contour that lasts all day. It's great for creating a flawless, sculpted look, and the skin-smoothing benefits add extra appeal. While it's a bit of an investment, many users feel that the performance justifies the price. If you're looking for an easy, high-quality contour product, this one is definitely worth considering!
faceoff_positive.headline: Hollywood Contour Wand

faceoff_negative.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Charlotte Tilbury Hollywood Contour Wand in Medium is honestly so easy to use. The packaging is sleek, and I actually love the cushion tip, it makes dotting it on super simple. It blends nicely. I don't have to fight with it or spend forever buffing it out. It gives my skin that soft, sculpted look without doing the most.

The finish is really natural, almost skin-like with a little healthy glow. Nothing too dewy or too matte. I like that I can build it up if I want more definition without it looking harsh. No streaks, no blotchiness, just smooth.

And there's barely any scent, which I really appreciate. I'm sensitive to smells, and this one didn't bother me at all. I do wish the tube had a little more product for the price, but honestly, a little goes a long way. It's definitely become part of my routine.
faceoff_negative.headline: Good contour stick
